00:31:39,562 --> 00:31:43,125
but not getting a reward you expect can make a reward a penalty.

537
00:31:43,125 --> 00:31:47,088
So this is the idea that if you build something up as really big and important,

538
00:31:47,088 --> 00:31:52,633
like players go around and they pick up every single consumable and collectible in your entire game

539
00:31:52,633 --> 00:31:54,715
and they get nothing for it,

540
00:31:54,715 --> 00:31:59,679
this can feel like a bad thing if they were expecting something to come out at the end.

541
00:32:01,703 --> 00:32:06,504
The next is that task inherent rewards motivate more than task relevant.

542
00:32:06,504 --> 00:32:09,325
Or to put that more simply and basically,

543
00:32:09,325 --> 00:32:13,106
rewards that are meaningful to a player are more motivating.

544
00:32:13,106 --> 00:32:19,487
A classic example of this would be the agility orbs from the Xbox game Crackdown.

545
00:32:19,487 --> 00:32:23,528
These orbs, you had to show agility in order to get them.

546
00:32:23,528 --> 00:32:27,009
You had to climb up buildings, jump, and generally show that...

547
00:32:27,750 --> 00:32:30,892
you had agility and power in your character, but by collecting them

548
00:32:30,892 --> 00:32:35,074
you also increased your agility. So they had meaning in two ways to players.

549
00:32:35,074 --> 00:32:38,416
You showed competence in this to get them and then you're awarded by

550
00:32:38,416 --> 00:32:42,358
being able to do more of this, you got the progression of being able to do that.

551
00:32:42,358 --> 00:32:48,661
And one way you can do this in games is to personalize if you can, if you have

552
00:32:48,661 --> 00:32:52,263
data on what people are already doing in your game you can reward them in ways

553
00:32:52,263 --> 00:32:53,143
that you know

554
00:32:53,143 --> 00:32:55,824
will be rewarding to them because it's the type of thing they're already

555
00:32:55,824 --> 00:32:56,525
interested in.

556
00:32:57,454 --> 00:33:01,437
but you don't have to go that far. All you really have to do is show value.

557
00:33:01,437 --> 00:33:05,700
And when I was working as a consultant, this was often a problem we would see

558
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:08,443
in mobile games that would come to us, is in the tutorials

