00:33:08,443 --> 00:33:11,685
they would throw all their awards at the players. They would say,

560
00:33:11,685 --> 00:33:15,008
here's premium currency, here's this, skip this timer, all these things.

561
00:33:15,008 --> 00:33:17,831
And it was like, here's all the things, but we're not telling you why or what

562
00:33:17,831 --> 00:33:20,993
the meaning or what the value is. We're going to get you to skip a 30-second

563
00:33:20,993 --> 00:33:21,374
tutorial.

564
00:33:22,174 --> 00:33:24,715
Like, why is that important to somebody?

565
00:33:24,715 --> 00:33:26,856
And it doesn't, it hurts people's learning

566
00:33:26,856 --> 00:33:28,817
and it hurts the evaluation of the reward

567
00:33:28,817 --> 00:33:30,758
if the reward is not meaningful.

568
00:33:30,758 --> 00:33:35,700
Okay, interacting with others positively is motivating.

569
00:33:35,700 --> 00:33:37,941
And when I say positively, it's positive

570
00:33:37,941 --> 00:33:39,902
for at least one person in the equation.

571
00:33:39,902 --> 00:33:41,863
So if I beat someone at a game,

572
00:33:41,863 --> 00:33:44,744
it may not be positive for them, but it's positive for me.

573
00:33:44,744 --> 00:33:48,326
So, when you're interacting with others,

574
00:33:48,326 --> 00:33:49,846
you can do performance comparison.

575
00:33:50,417 --> 00:33:53,097
you can compare your performance against other people.

576
00:33:53,097 --> 00:33:55,297
And this is potentially rewarding if it's in our favor.

577
00:33:55,297 --> 00:33:58,958
It's also potentially motivating if it shows progress

578
00:33:58,958 --> 00:34:01,038
or changes expectations positively.

579
00:34:01,038 --> 00:34:04,139
So even if it's not in our favor, but it shows we made progress

580
00:34:04,139 --> 00:34:06,779
or it changes our expectations,

581
00:34:06,779 --> 00:34:09,220
like we did better than we thought we would, that can be good.

582
00:34:09,220 --> 00:34:12,741
But of course, it can be demotivating if it's against us

583
00:34:12,741 --> 00:34:14,661
or if it changes our expectations negatively.

584
00:34:14,661 --> 00:34:16,681
And I'm going to give you an example of this.

585
00:34:16,681 --> 00:34:18,642
It's not necessarily a reward example.

