00:36:40,098 --> 00:36:44,321
we often don't think about the losers in our games and how we can make losing a pleasant

626
00:36:44,321 --> 00:36:44,941
experience.

627
00:36:44,941 --> 00:36:51,025
An experience that we can let people learn from and come back from and feel like they

628
00:36:51,025 --> 00:36:55,248
can stay engaged with our game and don't just go, well this is over, I'm going to stop playing.

629
00:36:56,775 --> 00:37:02,696
Cooperation, on the other hand, compared to competition, is a very powerfully motivating

630
00:37:02,696 --> 00:37:03,916
factor for a lot of people.

631
00:37:03,916 --> 00:37:07,017
And that's because it allows everyone to contribute to it.

632
00:37:07,017 --> 00:37:12,158
Nearly every top game you can think of nowadays has some kind of cooperation element in it.

633
00:37:12,158 --> 00:37:17,459
Cooperation, according to psychological research, motivates people a lot more than competition,

634
00:37:17,459 --> 00:37:18,940
which has been shown to...

635
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:23,861
Competition has been shown to do things like suppress creativity, cause conflict, all these

636
00:37:23,861 --> 00:37:24,461
kind of things.

637
00:37:25,456 --> 00:37:30,362
And it does allow for cooperative competition where guilds can compete against each other.

638
00:37:30,362 --> 00:37:32,485
And this gets you kind of the best of both worlds.

639
00:37:32,485 --> 00:37:35,589
You've got the competition stuff but you've also got the cooperation between people.

640
00:37:36,620 --> 00:37:41,264
It allows for repossessity, which I can never say, but it's basically the idea that people

