00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:20,141
Now, before I finish up,

669
00:39:20,141 --> 00:39:22,741
I do want to just briefly talk about some cognitive biases,

670
00:39:22,741 --> 00:39:27,643
and only a couple of them that I feel can be important

671
00:39:27,643 --> 00:39:28,603
when it comes to reward.

672
00:39:28,603 --> 00:39:32,024
One of them is the representativeness heuristic.

673
00:39:32,879 --> 00:39:36,581
And this is the idea that the more time, cost, effort you put into an activity,

674
00:39:36,581 --> 00:39:41,044
there's a basic expectation that you get more reward for it.

675
00:39:41,044 --> 00:39:46,067
So imagine you're a relatively tough fighter in an RPG game,

676
00:39:46,067 --> 00:39:50,790
and you encounter an unconscious goblin,

677
00:39:50,790 --> 00:39:53,972
and you knock it out and kill it.

678
00:39:53,972 --> 00:39:56,273
You probably don't expect to get much reward from that.

679
00:39:56,273 --> 00:39:58,575
You haven't put much effort in, you haven't done very much.

680
00:39:59,275 --> 00:40:04,498
But if you fight something like this, you probably expect to get a lot more from beating it.

681
00:40:04,498 --> 00:40:12,463
And this is somewhat common sense, but it can be a problem for games that have a lot of randomness or procedural generation in them.

682
00:40:12,463 --> 00:40:17,146
I've played quite a few roguelikes where I'll go through a room that was really, really difficult

683
00:40:17,146 --> 00:40:20,848
because of the configuration of monsters in there or the way that it was laid out,

684
00:40:20,848 --> 00:40:24,451
and then the room on the other side is just an empty hallway with nothing in it.

685
00:40:24,931 --> 00:40:28,895
And that feels against expectations, against this heuristic, that if I've put effort in,

686
00:40:28,895 --> 00:40:31,477
I expect that effort to be rewarded.

687
00:40:31,477 --> 00:40:37,422
So this can be taken into account with the reward systems also being tied to the randomization

688
00:40:37,422 --> 00:40:39,404
or the proceduralization that comes out at the end.

689
00:40:39,404 --> 00:40:44,008
If it's over a certain amount of difficulty, then there should be more reward for doing it.

690
00:40:45,972 --> 00:40:48,153
This can also apply to monetization.

