00:45:39,491 --> 00:45:43,212
To go over what I've gone over today, reward is feedback.

777
00:45:43,212 --> 00:45:46,392
Please do provide feedback on rewards as close to the behaviors

778
00:45:46,392 --> 00:45:48,773
you want to reward as possible.

779
00:45:48,773 --> 00:45:51,133
For long-term rewards, this can be progression towards them.

780
00:45:51,133 --> 00:45:54,934
Mix certain guaranteed rewards with rewards that feel more random

781
00:45:54,934 --> 00:45:59,215
and unexpected to get different types of behaviors,

782
00:45:59,215 --> 00:46:01,796
to get different kinds of response rates.

783
00:46:01,796 --> 00:46:04,437
Control and value. Help players feel in control.

784
00:46:05,247 --> 00:46:08,008
This does not mean not guiding them or teaching them,

785
00:46:08,008 --> 00:46:10,549
but help them be able to access your game

786
00:46:10,549 --> 00:46:15,271
and get at the rewards and not feel controlled by those rewards.

787
00:46:15,271 --> 00:46:18,212
And show the value of the rewards and behavior,

788
00:46:18,212 --> 00:46:20,112
which can often be a good way to reduce control.

789
00:46:20,112 --> 00:46:22,833
When we talk about social rewards,

790
00:46:22,833 --> 00:46:27,375
comparison, competition and cooperation can motivate,

791
00:46:27,375 --> 00:46:28,575
but they do come with risks.

792
00:46:29,391 --> 00:46:33,892
Really, try and think about the players in your games that are losing out on your competitions,

793
00:46:33,892 --> 00:46:39,353
or not coming in first place, or consistently not showing any performance increases.

794
00:46:39,353 --> 00:46:46,594
By giving these players some way to stay motivated, some way to still feel in control, to feel

795
00:46:46,594 --> 00:46:51,255
like they can progress, you can keep them in your game and keep them retained.

796
00:46:51,255 --> 00:46:57,016
Social pressure and cooperation to do things like give gifts to other players or work together,

797
00:46:57,016 --> 00:46:57,816
it can be good.

798
00:47:00,016 --> 00:47:03,058
If it's presented wrong, it can also feel like control,

799
00:47:03,058 --> 00:47:05,039
which may cause people to abandon it.

800
00:47:05,039 --> 00:47:08,161
And you should set and meet player expectations.

801
00:47:08,161 --> 00:47:11,603
Try and understand what these expectations that you're setting up

802
00:47:11,603 --> 00:47:13,044
may be unintentionally,

803
00:47:13,044 --> 00:47:15,006
and at least meet them, if not exceed them.

804
00:47:15,006 --> 00:47:19,288
And preventing loss can motivate more than working for gain.

